 A massive
explosion damaged and partially collapsed a unit at of the Astron Energy
plants. In the
early morning of Thursday, the Milnerton plant exploded and it is not clear if
there are any casualties. In a
statement, Astron Energy South Africa confirmed that an incident occurred at
its Milnerton Refinery at approximately 4.00 am on 2 July 2020. “Astron
Energy immediately activated its emergency response procedures and notified the
relevant authorities,” said the company. The
resultant fire has been contained and the plant is now stable.  “Our
priority is to ensure the safety of all those on-site and further information
will be provided as soon as we have confirmed the details,” Astron added. 